The as-prepared Al-N@CQDs (600 µL, 0.15 mg mL−1) were thoroughly mixed with GSH@CuNCs (400 µL, 0.45 mg mL−1) and Tris HCl buffer (pH 6.0, 700 µL). The resultant mixture was allowed to stand at room temperature for 2 min. After that, 300 µL of various concentrations of P2O7
                        4− were added and incubated for further 2 min. Finally, the fluorescence emission readings were recorded at 450 nm and 620 nm after excitation at 310 nm (Scheme 1
                        ).
